WHO WE ARE

About Evertree

At Evertree, we double down on the belief that good humans make great leaders. That’s why we’ve purposely pinpointed luminaries in our space to guide us on our mission.

Good humans like our founder, Alex Tuff. With funding from experienced insurance industry investors, Integrum Holdings, Alex has the support to continue the positive growth of Evertree through the acquisition of top tier agencies, development of a new technology platform, and recruitment of best-in-class personal lines producers — creating a better tomorrow for both our employees and our customers.

FOUNDER & CEO

    Alex Tuff

    Meet Alex, the visionary behind Evertree Insurance, bringing over two decades of executive expertise to the table. Alex’s journey is one of continuous growth, innovation, and leadership across various sectors. With a robust background in scaling companies, strategic planning, tech systems, leadership alignment, capital ventures, and financial revamps, Alex’s career is a testament to his dedication and skill.

    Before the inception of Evertree in 2022, Alex played a pivotal role as President of Winged Keel Group, steering the company onto the national stage with strategic acquisitions and the opening of new offices populated with freshly minted talent. Not stopping there, Alex lent his expertise as Partner and Advisor to SALI Fund Services, contributing to its growth until its acquisition by JTC in 2021. Prior to Winged Keel Group, Alex held leadership positions at CIT Group and American Express.

    Beyond the boardroom, Alex contributes to the community as a board member of Open Doors Shelter in Norwalk, CT, and engages with fellow leaders as a member of the Young Presidents Organization (YPO). EVERTREE CHAIRWOMAN

    Ursula Burns

    Ursula Burns is the Chairwoman of the Evertree Board of Directors. Ms. Burns was the Chairwoman of the Board of Xerox Corporation from 2010 to 2017 and Chief Executive Officer from 2009 to 2016 after being appointed President in 2007. After retiring from Xerox, Ms. Burns was appointed Chairwoman of VEON, Ltd. in 2017. Ms. Burns became its Chairwoman and CEO in December 2018 until June 2020. Burns is a founding partner of Integrum Holdings, a private equity firm and Non-Executive Chairwoman of Teneo Holdings LLC. She is also a member of the Uber Technologies, Inc. and IHS Holding Ltd. boards of directors. Ms. Burns previously served on the boards of directors of Nestle S.A. and American Express. In addition, Ms. Burns is on several private company boards, including Waystar, while also providing leadership counsel to several other community, educational, and non-profit organizations, including the Ford Foundation, the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT) Corporation, the Metropolitan Museum of Art and the Mayo Clinic, amongst others. In addition to her corporate leadership roles, U.S. President Barack Obama appointed Burns to lead the White House national program on Science, Technology, Engineering and Math (STEM) from 2009 to 2016, and Ms. Burns served as Chair of the President’s Export Council from 2015 to 2016 after service as Vice Chair from 2010 to 2015. In February 2022, Burns joined the U.S. Department of Commerce’s Advisory Council on Supply Chain Competitiveness as Vice Chair. Her book “Where You Are Is Not Who You Are” was published in June 2021.

    Senior Accountant

    • SEATTLE, WA

    • 07/24/2024

        

    The Company: 

    We are committed to leveraging cutting-edge technology and strategic growth initiatives to revolutionize the insurance industry. Funded with over $130MM from one of the top private equity firms in the country, Evertree Insurance is a rapidly expanding national independent insurance agency that specializes in providing comprehensive personal lines insurance solutions to clients across the country. Founded in 2022, the company now employs over 220 people across Mid-Atlantic, Northeast, and Mountain Regions and is a top 30 personal lines brokerage firm in the country. As a leader in the insurance sector, we are dedicated to delivering exceptional service and tailored coverage options to meet our clients' diverse personal and commercial lines needs.


    The Position: 

    The Senior Accountant will be responsible for maintaining the financial health of the company through detailed and thorough accounting practices and insightful financial reporting.


    Cultural Fit:

    Evertree is a dynamic and rapidly growing company, experiencing over 20% growth across two revenue channels: retail and embedded solutions. The Corporate team is a youthful, diverse team with deep expertise in respective functions, we seek a Senior Accountant who can be a subject matter expert and a strong cultural fit for our next-generation team.


    The Day-To-Day:

    • Financial Reporting:
      • Prepare accurate and timely financial statements and reports.
      • Ensure compliance with GAAP and other regulatory requirements.
    • General Ledger:
      • Maintain and reconcile general ledger accounts.
      • Manage month-end and year-end closing processes.
    • Accounts Payable/Receivable:
      • Oversee AP and AR functions.
      • Ensure timely and accurate processing of invoices and payments.
    • Budgeting and Forecasting:
      • Assist in the preparation of annual budgets and financial forecasts.
      • Monitor budget performance and provide variance analysis.
    • Audit Support:
      • Assist with internal and external audits.
      • Ensure all audit requirements are met and documentation is accurate.
    • Financial Analysis:
      • Conduct financial analysis to support business decisions.
      • Provide insights and recommendations to senior management.
    • Process Improvement:
      • Identify opportunities for process improvements and efficiencies.
      • Implement best practices in accounting and financial reporting.

    How do I file a claim?

    Please contact your insurance carrier directly if you have a claim and they will advise you on the best plan of action. However, if you have any questions please contact your agent directly. We are happy to help you through the process!

    READ MORE

    How do I pay my bill?

    Most insurance carriers allow you to pay online. Here are the payment links for some of our carriers:

    • Travelers
    • Grange
    • Progressive
    • Main Street America
    • Hanover

    If you can’t find your policy number or carrier, please contact your agent directly. We are happy to help you through the process!

    READ MORE

    How do I get my auto ID cards?

    Most carriers have mobile apps you can use to request your ID cards. The best way to determine if your carrier has a mobile app is to simply Google them. You will likely be instructed to create a customer login. Once you’re set up, you will be able to request your ID cards.

    If you have any questions please contact your agent directly.

    READ MORE

    How do I change my mortgage company?

    If your mortgage company has changed, simply give your agent a call to let us know. Changes are a common occurrence, and most mortgage companies do not inform the insurance carriers when they make a switch. It’s very important for us to have the correct mortgage information on the insurance policy so your coverage doesn’t get interrupted.

    READ MORE

    How do I add someone to my policy?

    Give your agent call. We ask that you have the following information handy because we are going to ask for it.

    Policy holder’s name and the name of the driver you would like to add.
    Policy number or address.
    What cars are being removed or added (if any) and their VIN numbers.
    Specify coverage - will you need more? You can also choose to keep it the same as the other vehicles on your policy.

    READ MORE

    Should I file a claim?

    Here are some things to consider if you are deciding whether to file a claim:

    Was anyone injured?
    Did you damage someone else’s property or vehicle?
    Is it unsafe to live in your home or drive your car?
    Are the damages above your deductible?
    Is it just a maintenance issue or normal wear-and-tear?

    If you answered yes to one or more of these questions, you should consider filing a claim. That way we can begin collecting the information needed to resolve your claim quickly. If you have questions about filing a claim, call our service department at (757) 448-3820 to speak to a dedicated Claims Advocate or contact your carrier directly.

    In the meantime, browse our claims resources below to find guidance on the most frequently asked questions.
